<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>PyVoice — Python Voice-to-Code</title>
<meta name="description" content="Write Python by speaking. PyVoice converts natural speech into valid Python code with automatic syntax correction.">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=JetBrains+Mono:ital,wght@0,300;0,400;0,500;0,700;1,400&family=Syne:wght@400;600;700;800&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<link rel="stylesheet" href="css/style.css">
</head>
<body>

<div id="app">

  <!-- TITLEBAR -->
  <header id="titlebar">
    <div class="logo">py<span>voice</span></div>
    <nav class="tb-nav">
      <span class="tb-badge">v1.0 · free &amp; open source</span>
    </nav>
    <div class="tb-spacer"></div>
    <div id="status-indicator">
      <span class="status-dot" id="status-dot"></span>
      <span id="status-text">ready</span>
    </div>
    <button class="tb-btn" onclick="showHelp()">? help</button>
  </header>

  <!-- MAIN EDITOR -->
  <main id="main-editor">
    <div id="editor-tabs">
      <div class="tab active">
        <span class="tab-dot"></span>main.py
      </div>
      <div class="editor-actions">
        <button class="icon-btn" onclick="copyCode()" title="Copy all code">⎘ copy</button>
        <button class="icon-btn" onclick="downloadCode()" title="Download as .py file">↓ download .py</button>
        <button class="icon-btn" onclick="clearCode()" title="Clear all">✕ clear</button>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div id="code-scroll">
      <div id="gutter"></div>
      <div id="code-lines">
        <div id="empty-state">
          <svg width="52" height="52" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.2" aria-hidden="true">
            <path d="M12 1a3 3 0 0 0-3 3v8a3 3 0 0 0 6 0V4a3 3 0 0 0-3-3z"/>
            <path d="M19 10v2a7 7 0 0 1-14 0v-2"/>
            <line x1="12" y1="19" x2="12" y2="23"/>
            <line x1="8" y1="23" x2="16" y2="23"/>
          </svg>
          <p>Speak into the mic, or type below to generate Python</p>
          <p class="empty-hint">Try: <em>"def greet function that takes name and prints hello name"</em></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <!-- SIDEBAR -->
  <aside id="sidebar">

    <!-- VOICE SECTION -->
    <section class="sb-section" id="voice-wrap">
      <div class="sb-header">Voice Input</div>
      <div id="voice-section">
        <button id="mic-btn" onclick="toggleMic()" aria-label="Toggle microphone">
          <span class="mic-ring" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          <span id="mic-label">Start Listening</span>
        </button>
        <div id="transcript-area" aria-live="polite">Your speech appears here…</div>
        <div id="voice-actions">
          <button class="voice-btn" onclick="clearTranscript()">clear</button>
          <button class="voice-btn primary" id="insert-btn" disabled onclick="insertTranscript()">→ convert &amp; insert</button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- QUICK COMMANDS -->
    <section class="sb-section" id="commands-wrap">
      <div class="sb-header">Voice Commands</div>
      <div id="commands-list">
        <div class="cmd-row"><code>"def greet function"</code><span>→ def with ():  </span></div>
        <div class="cmd-row"><code>"for i in range 10"</code><span>→ for loop</span></div>
        <div class="cmd-row"><code>"if x equals 5"</code><span>→ if x == 5:</span></div>
        <div class="cmd-row"><code>"print hello world"</code><span>→ print("hello world")</span></div>
        <div class="cmd-row"><code>"open paren / close paren"</code><span>→ ( )</span></div>
        <div class="cmd-row"><code>"indent / new line"</code><span>→ spaces / \n</span></div>
        <div class="cmd-row"><code>"import numpy as np"</code><span>→ import statement</span></div>
        <div class="cmd-row"><code>"return x plus y"</code><span>→ return x + y</span></div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- LINE EDITOR -->
    <section class="sb-section" id="edit-wrap" style="flex:1;display:flex;flex-direction:column;overflow:hidden;">
      <div class="sb-header">Line Editor</div>
      <div id="edit-inner">
        <div class="edit-label">selected line</div>
        <div id="selected-line-preview" class="preview-empty">← click a line to select it</div>
        <div class="edit-label" style="margin-top:10px">quick edits</div>
        <div id="quick-edits">
          <button class="qe-btn" onclick="quickEdit('add type hints')">+ type hints</button>
          <button class="qe-btn" onclick="quickEdit('add docstring')">+ docstring</button>
          <button class="qe-btn" onclick="quickEdit('convert to list comprehension')">list comp</button>
          <button class="qe-btn" onclick="quickEdit('add default parameter value of None')">+ default arg</button>
          <button class="qe-btn" onclick="quickEdit('wrap in try except block')">try/except</button>
          <button class="qe-btn" onclick="quickEdit('make async')">async</button>
        </div>
        <div class="edit-label" style="margin-top:10px">manual fix (regex/replace)</div>
        <div id="find-replace">
          <input id="find-input" type="text" placeholder="find…" spellcheck="false">
          <input id="replace-input" type="text" placeholder="replace with…" spellcheck="false">
          <button class="fr-btn" onclick="doFindReplace()">replace in line</button>
        </div>
        <div id="edit-log">Select a line to enable editing.</div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </aside>

  <!-- BOTTOM BAR -->
  <footer id="bottombar">
    <span class="bb-prompt">›</span>
    <input id="cmd-input" type="text"
      placeholder="Type in plain English or Python — e.g. 'def add function takes a and b returns a plus b'"
      onkeydown="if(event.key==='Enter')handleCmdInput()"
      spellcheck="false"
      autocomplete="off">
    <button id="cmd-btn" onclick="handleCmdInput()">convert &amp; add</button>
  </footer>

</div>

<!-- HELP MODAL -->
<div id="help-overlay" onclick="hideHelp()" style="display:none">
  <div id="help-modal" onclick="event.stopPropagation()">
    <div class="hm-header">
      <span class="hm-title">How to use PyVoice</span>
      <button onclick="hideHelp()" class="hm-close">✕</button>
    </div>
    <div class="hm-body">
      <h3>Voice Input</h3>
      <p>Click <strong>Start Listening</strong> and speak naturally. The app uses your browser's built-in speech recognition (no server needed). When you're done, click <strong>convert &amp; insert</strong> to turn it into Python.</p>
      <h3>Text Input</h3>
      <p>Type plain English in the bottom bar and press Enter. The engine will parse it into Python with correct syntax automatically.</p>
      <h3>Line Editing</h3>
      <p>Click any line to select it. Use quick-edit buttons or find/replace to modify it. Hover a line for move/delete controls.</p>
      <h3>Syntax Engine</h3>
      <p>The converter handles: function definitions, loops, conditionals, print statements, imports, operators, punctuation keywords (open paren, colon, etc.), indentation, and more — all in JavaScript, no API key required.</p>
      <h3>Browser Support</h3>
      <p>Voice recognition works best in <strong>Chrome</strong> or <strong>Edge</strong>. Make sure microphone access is allowed in browser settings, and that Windows Settings → Privacy → Microphone has your browser enabled.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div id="toast" role="status" aria-live="polite"></div>

<script src="js/syntax.js"></script>
<script src="js/highlight.js"></script>
<script src="js/app.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
